---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const criteria = [
  'Clear pet policy, not hidden negotiation.',
  'Outdoor space or easy walking access nearby.',
  'A location that still makes the Peninsula easy to do with a dog in the car.',
  'Enough comfort that the stay still feels like a trip, not a compromise.',
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Dog-Friendly Accommodation Mornington Peninsula | Peninsula Insider" description="The practical Peninsula Insider guide to dog-friendly accommodation on the Mornington Peninsula." section="stay" ogImage="/images/sourced/dog-lifestyle-hero-01.webp">
  <main class="article-shell container prose" style="padding: 3rem 0 4rem; max-width: 820px;">
    <p class="label label--accent">Dog-Friendly Peninsula</p>
    <h1>Dog-Friendly Accommodation on the Mornington Peninsula</h1>
    <p><img src="/images/sourced/dog-lifestyle-hero-01.webp" alt="Dog relaxing during a weekend stay" style="width:100%; border-radius: 18px; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; object-fit: cover;" /></p>
    <p>The right dog-friendly stay is not just one that allows pets. It is one that still makes the trip feel worth taking. That means less emphasis on pet-policy copy and more emphasis on whether the base actually works for the weekend you want.</p>
    <h2>The filter</h2>
    <ul>
      {criteria.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
    </ul>
    <p>This should become a proper set of Peninsula Insider stay picks, grouped by trip shape and geography.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
